                  <ref eId="c00002" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1948/29">1948 c.29</ref> (11 and 12 Geo. 6 c.29) (“the 1948 Act”). Section 22(5) was relevantly amended by the Social Security Act <ref eId="c00003" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1980/30">1980 (c.30)</ref>, schedule 4, paragraph 2(1). The functions of the Secretary of State so far as exercisable within devolved competence were transferred to the Scottish Ministers by section 53 of the Scotland Act <ref eId="c00004" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1998/46">1998 (c.46)</ref>.</p>
